	<p class="lead-italic">
		Commonwealth Audiology performs real ear measurements as part of hearing
		aid fitting best practices.
	</p>
	<p>
		A Real Ear Measurement (REM) is a precise, in-office test that allows us to
		verify exactly how your hearing aids are performing in your ears, not just
		based on a computer estimate.
	</p>
	<p>
		During REM, a very thin, soft tube (microphone) is gently placed into your
		ear canal alongside your hearing aid. This microphone measures how sound is
		actually being delivered inside your ear while the hearing aid is on.
		Because every ear canal is shaped differently, this step ensures that the
		sound reaching your eardrum is accurate for you.
	</p>
	<p>
		Think of it as the difference between guessing and truly knowing. While
		hearing aids are programmed based on your hearing test, REM confirms that
		you're receiving the right amount of amplification at each pitch, so speech
		is clear, sounds are balanced, and nothing is too soft or too loud.
	</p>
	<p>
		For you as the patient, it's quick, comfortable, and incredibly important.
		It's one of the key steps that helps your hearing aids feel more natural
		and perform their best in everyday situations.
	</p>

